   VERSION=( "0.5.2" "0.5.1" "0.5.0" "0.4.17" )
  CATEGORY="email office"
 ATTRIBUTE="console"
       URL="$SOURCEFORGE_URL"
    SOURCE="abook/abook-$VERSION"
       REQ="ncurses readline"
    OPT[0]="mutt:::for mutt integration"
  HOMEPAGE="http://abook.sourceforge.net"
 FRESHMEAT="abook"
  ESTIMATE="24"
     SHORT="abook is an address book program with mutt mail client support."
      LONG="
abook is a text-based addressbook program 
designed to use with mutt mail client.

If you want to use abook with mutt you should add following lines 
to your  ~/.muttrc or to the system wide /etc/Muttrc file.

set query_command="abook --mutt-query '%s'"
macro pager A |'abook --add-email'\n

After this you can make queries from 
mutt using the query command ('Q')
and add sender e-mail addresses to the
addressbook from pager using 'A' command. 
"
